# Flutter Development Rules

## Structure

- Player app: `lib/features/` for features; `lib/shared/` for shared UI; `lib/core/` for global services
- Admin app: `lib/modules/` for modules; `lib/core/` for global services
- Environment config: `lib/core/environment/` — no hardcoded Firebase project IDs in feature code
- Support `dev`, `staging`, `prod` flavours with `REVO_ENV` dart-define

## Language

- Sound null safety (required)
- Explicit return types
- `const` constructors where appropriate
- Immutable data models where practical
- Named parameters for complex constructors
- Sealed classes or enums for finite states
- Typed exceptions and failure objects
- Repository abstraction for data access

Avoid: `dynamic` (unless integration requires it), excessive `late`, forced `!`, business logic in `build()`, giant stateful widgets, fire-and-forget futures, uncontrolled singletons, direct Firestore from presentation widgets.

## Null safety

Never use `!` merely to silence analysis errors. Validate presence, use nullable types when absence is valid, return structured errors when absence is invalid.

```dart
// Wrong
final game = gameSnapshot.data!;

// Preferred
final game = gameSnapshot.data;
if (game == null) {
  return const GameLoadFailureView();
}
```

## Screen state

Every remote-data screen must support: `initial`, `loading`, `success`, `empty`, `error`, `unauthorized`, `offline` (where relevant). Never show a blank page on failure.

## Navigation

Use centralized route definitions. Protected routes must check authentication, role, permission, institution scope, and feature availability. Hiding a menu item is not sufficient authorization.

## Firebase access (client)

**May:** read authorized data, submit through approved repositories, call trusted Cloud Functions, upload permitted media, listen to permitted real-time updates.

**Must not:** assign custom claims, finalize official results, write official rank, award medals, activate production game builds, change protected tournament rules, approve privileged roles.

## WebView (Unity)

- Use approved game URLs; validate environment, game ID and version
- Restrict navigation; handle loading timeout and bridge errors
- Restore device orientation; dispose resources correctly
- Never expose privileged tokens in URL
- Use versioned Flutter–Unity protocol

## Localization

User-facing text must use localization keys (see rule 13). No hardcoded English in production UI paths.

## Naming

- Files: `lower_snake_case.dart`
- Classes: `UpperCamelCase`
- Variables: `lowerCamelCase`
- Private fields: `_lowerCamelCase`

## Review checklist

- [ ] Null safety preserved
- [ ] Loading / empty / error states present
- [ ] No privileged client writes
- [ ] Localization keys used
- [ ] Widget complexity within limits (rule 11)
